name: glass wool mat production | glass wool mat | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/10683/documentation

This module can be used for all different kind of glass wool mats. The density of the glass wool mat used as basis for the study is 40 kg/m3.;The original dataset from ecoinvent v2 has been ammended with CO2 and NOx emissions.;Child dataset exchanges identical to GLO dataset. Created to enable linking to regional markets (e.g. for electricity). Data quality indicators adjusted accordingly.

Included processes: melting, fibre forming & collecting, hardening & curing and internal processes (workshop, etc.). Additionally, energy carrier for furnace, packing and infrastructure are included.

The activity ends with the product being ready to be shipped.
category: C:Manufacturing/23:Manufacture of other non-metallic mineral products/239:Manufacture of non-metallic mineral products n.e.c./2399:Manufacture of other non-metallic mineral products n.e.c.

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data are only from one company in Switzerland (Isover SA). ;Child dataset exchanges identical to GLO dataset. Created to enable linking to regional markets (e.g. for electricity). Data quality indicators adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: The company worked on a very high technical level but the data refer to the situation before 1995. The energy for the melting process is mainly electricity and from natural gas. The amount of waste glass used as raw material is about 65%.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: see Geography and Technology The original data is for geography CH, which was extrapolated to GLO. This child dataset exchanges identical to GLO dataset. Created to enable linking to regional markets (e.g. for electricity). Data quality indicators adjusted accordingly.
